{"Id":"7e7f491f-b200-43bf-8254-d8a63df40731","Title":"Adafruit I2S Mic -  SPH0645","Description":"<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd\">\n<html><head><meta name=\"qrichtext\" content=\"1\" /><style type=\"text/css\">\np, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }\n</style></head><body style=\" font-family:'MS Shell Dlg 2'; font-size:8.25pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;\">\n<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\">For many microcontrollers, <a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/products/1063\"><span style=\" text-decoration: underline; color:#0000ff;\">adding audio input is easy with one of our analog microphone breakouts</span></a>. But as you get to bigger and better microcontrollers and microcomputers, you'll find that you don't always have an analog input, or maybe you want to avoid the noise that can seep in with an analog mic system. Once you get past 8-bit micros, you will often find an <span style=\" font-weight:600;\">I2S</span> peripheral, that can take <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">digital audio data</span> in! That's where this <span style=\" font-weight:600;\">I2S Microphone Breakout</span> comes in.</p>\n<p style=\"-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\"><br /></p>\n<p style=\" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\">Instead of an analog output, there are three digital pins: Clock, Data and Word-Select. When connected to your microcontroller/computer, the 'I2S Master' will drive the clock and word-select pins at a high frequency and read out the data from the microphone. No analog conversion required!</p></body></html>","Author":"ladyada","Source":"Fritzing library 'AdaFruit.fzbz'","Properties":{"fritzingModelIndex":"85434093","variant":"variant 1","family":"Adafruit I2S Mic -  SPH0645","part number":"Adafruit #3421","layer":null,"fritzingVersion":"0.5.2b.02.18.4756","fritzingPartVersion":"4","fritzingDate":"Wed Feb 22 2017","fritzingModuleId":"adafruit_4a34a67fa13f20e5334e6a2db3ed98fc_4"},"Tags":[],"Views":{"breadboard":{"ViewType":"breadboard","ViewImageRef":"breadboard\\adafruit_4a34a67fa13f20e5334e6a2db3ed98fc_7_breadboard.xaml","NativeWidthInInches":0.65,"NativeHeightInInches":0.5,"Layers":{}},"schematic":{"ViewType":"schematic","ViewImageRef":"schematic\\adafruit_4a34a67fa13f20e5334e6a2db3ed98fc_7_schematic.xaml","NativeWidthInInches":1.2,"NativeHeightInInches":1.0,"Layers":{}},"pcb":{"ViewType":"pcb","ViewImageRef":"pcb\\adafruit_4a34a67fa13f20e5334e6a2db3ed98fc_7_pcb.xaml","NativeWidthInInches":0.65,"NativeHeightInInches":0.5,"Layers":{}}}}